records.addlTxt:
Defendant Randolph J Sottile in court with attorney Katie B. Kegel.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern and supervising attorney Jack Pitzo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State makes sentencing recommendation.  Defense makes sentencing recommendation.  Defendant makes statement.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 2 days)
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S)

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent.

If the defendant has any drug related infraction during the course of probation, the DOC should immediately seek revocation of probation.  

REIMBURSEMENT:  $250.00 to Waukesha Metro Drug Unit (apply cash bail);  

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (apply cash bail);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
